# Chroma Modular WF - How to use

## Chroma models
You need to download the latest Chroma model from [here](https://huggingface.co/lodestones/Chroma/tree/main) . Always select the latest version.

There are also the FP8 and Quantized version if you have less than 24Gb Vram.  [FP8 version](https://huggingface.co/Clybius/Chroma-fp8-scaled/tree/main) or [Quantized version](https://huggingface.co/silveroxides/Chroma-GGUF/tree/main)

Clip and Vae are the same for FLUX. You can download the Clip from [here](https://huggingface.co/comfyanonymous/flux_text_encoders/resolve/main/t5xxl_fp16.safetensors?download=true), and the Vae from [here](https://huggingface.co/Comfy-Org/Lumina_Image_2.0_Repackaged/resolve/main/split_files/vae/ae.safetensors)

---

## Select the workflow and the modules

Go to the Switches group and select between the Standard (txt2img or img2img) workflow or the Inpaint workflow.

Next, you should select what modules you want to use.  I suggest to start generating only with the basic workflow, without any module active.  Once you find a good prompt and the right settings, you can start develop your image by using HiRes Fix, the Upscaler and the other modules.  PostProduction module is always active, but you can use the settings shown in the notes if you don't want to apply any Postproduction to the image.  Last, you can chose if you want to save the image with all the metadata (for example if you want to upload the image on CivitAI), and also you can choose if you want to save each single output from each module of the workflow too.

In the Image Comparer settings choose which images you want to compare in the large Preview node in the middle of the workflow.  (Hint:  if you keep the seeds fixed, you can change the preview quickly, without the need to re-generate the images)

*Remember you can navigate the workflow pressing "1" to go to the Frontend part of it, or pressing "2" to go to the Backend part of the wf.*

### Inpaint
The Inpaint workflow uses the same Chroma model as the standard workflow, so it's more a miss&hit workflow.  You will have to test many different seeds and settings to get a valid output. (Flux uses Flux.1 Fill as inpaint model).
Use around 0.60-0.70 denoise value, and play with different Inpaint settings.  Mask and prompt are very important too.
You will need to Load an image and draw a mask on it, where you want to apply Inpaint: right click on the loaded image, select "Open in Mask editor" and draw the mask. 
Inpaint will not work with HiRes-Fix module, at least I could not find any settings to make it work, you can play with it if you want... but since the Inpaint latent image is very peculiar it makes sense that it will not work.

---

## Prompt and settings
Now it's time to input your prompts (positive and negative), and to set up the many workflow's settings. The size of the image you want to generate, the number of steps, the cfg (stay around 4.00-6.00), the sampler and scheduler, the seed (random, fixed), the batch size, the denoise (use 1.00 for txt2img generation, around 0.40-0.60 for img2img generation).  You can use the DetailDaemon node (set detail_amount to 0.00 to turn it off, suggested value is 0.10).  Then you can select LoRAs' and their strength (you can get info about each lora you use from CivitAI too: right-click on the Lora and select "Show Info").  You can also set the Inpaint blur settings if you are using Inpaint workflow.

---

## Generate your image
Just press "Run" and wait to see your output image.  Beware, Chorma is still in the training process, so its model is not finished yet (today we are at v.35) and it may need a lot of Vram to output an image.  It may be very slow.  

On [Runpod](https://runpod.io?ref=9n2q5pa8), using my [Template](https://runpod.io/console/deploy?template=fnox0jr8pw&ref=9n2q5pa8) I get around 1.30s/it with a L40 GPU. 

Locally, on a rtx 4070 Ti Super (16Gb Vram) I get around 3.10s/it using the FP8 model and t5xxl clip.

---

## Modules available

### HiRes-Fix
Just a small "upscaler" that apply a little upscale to the latent adding also some new details.  Use a small upscale ratio (I suggest between 1.2x - 1.5x, but you can go up to 2.0x).  Denoise and number of steps may have to be fine-tuned according to the images you are working on.

### FaceDetailer
If your image show human faces, this module will try to improve the details and the quality of that part of the image.  There is no standard settings for this module.  You should test different steps, cfg and denoise.  Try also to change Cycle from default 1 to 2 or higher (but it will take longer to complete the generation).

### Ultimate SD Upscaler
In this module you can also use a "Skin-enhancer" model if your image is a realistic portrait.  The skin appearance and details will improve a lot.  You can download here the [1x-ITF-SkinDiffDetail](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/upscale_models/x1_ITF_SkinDiffDetail_Lite_v1.pth?download=true) model.  Save it in the /models/upscale_models/ folder.  I suggest to use the new [4xUltrasharp_v2](https://huggingface.co/Tenofas/ComfyUI/resolve/main/upscale_models/4x-UltraSharpV2.safetensors?download=true) upscale model as a all-around upscaler.

### Overlay Settings
This is only for testing purposes.  This module will write all the settings used in the generation over the image itself, so you can have a quick reference about what you used to generate that image.

### Save Image with Metadata
This module will save the final image (only) with all the metadata about the prompts and settings used in the generation.  This is very useful if you want to keep all these info on your outputs or if you want to upload the image on websites like CivitAI.

---

## Suggested settings
Personally I am getting great results using **res_multistep** as sampler and **beta** as scheduler, with cfg set a 4.00 and 30 or more steps.  Euler or Euler_ancestral with Beta should also give good results. Try to play with cfg, changing it from 4.00 up to 7.50 you will get very different results.

---

For any other information you can contact me on my [Patreon page](https://www.patreon.com/c/Tenofas), where all my Workflows will always be free for all!  Or on my [CivitAI page](https://civitai.com/user/Tenofas).
